      <h2>Airlines Flying Nonstop from Toronto to New York</h2><ul><li><strong>Air Canada</strong> — Multiple daily flights from YYZ to JFK, LGA, and EWR</li><li><strong>Porter Airlines</strong> — Multiple daily flights from Billy Bishop (YTZ) to Newark (EWR) — a highly convenient city-centre to city-centre option</li><li><strong>American Airlines</strong> — Daily service from YYZ to JFK and LGA</li><li><strong>Delta Air Lines</strong> — Daily service from YYZ to JFK and LGA</li><li><strong>United Airlines</strong> — Daily service from YYZ to EWR</li></ul><h2>Porter Airlines: The City-Centre Option</h2><p>Porter Airlines operates from Billy Bishop Toronto City Airport (YTZ) — a small island airport accessible by ferry right from downtown Toronto — to Newark Liberty (EWR), which connects directly to Manhattan via the AirTrain and NJ Transit. For travelers staying in downtown Toronto or Manhattan, this is arguably the most convenient door-to-door option, often beating the suburban airport experience despite a slightly longer flight time.</p><div class='info-box'><p>ℹ️ Porter flights are popular with business travelers specifically because of the downtown airport convenience. Book early — Porter's YTZ–EWR routes sell out quickly, particularly on Monday morning and Friday evening departures.</p></div><h2>Tips for Toronto to New York Nonstop</h2><ul><li>The short flight time (1.5 hours) makes this a natural day-trip or overnight-trip destination from either city — the nonstop makes it even easier.</li><li>NEXUS card holders have expedited customs at Pearson — sign up if you cross the border regularly.</li><li>Air Canada's Aeroplan miles have poor redemption value on short-haul routes — consider cash fares or Porter's own loyalty program for this corridor.</li></ul>
